div.div:
Address decoding is implemented by the FPGA.
In addition to controlling enable lines, the FPGA intercepts A[11:10] to implement mirroring for VRAM.
40 col: R11 = L, R10 = L
80 col: R11 = L
The FPGA also intercepts A15 and drives A16 to implement bank switching to access the upper 64KB.
Block 0/2: R16 = H, R15 = L
Block 1/3: R16 = H, R15 = H
